# AGENTS.md

## Purpose

This repository uses an AI Development Framework. Core logic lives in `ai-framework/`.
IDE adapters: `.cursor/rules/` (Cursor) and `.github/` (Copilot).

Every AI agent must read this file before planning, editing, testing, validating, or documenting.

**Project language:** {{PROJECT_LANGUAGE}} — all project artifacts in this language only (never mixed).

## Mandatory startup sequence

1. Read `PROJECT_PARAMETERS.md`
2. Read `ai-framework/README.md`
3. Read `ai-framework/core/methodology.md`
4. Read the relevant workflow from `ai-framework/workflows/`
5. Read the relevant agent role from `ai-framework/agents/`
6. Read applicable standards from `ai-framework/standards/`
7. Read applicable templates from `ai-framework/templates/`
8. Produce a concise execution plan before editing files

## Project structure

```text
01_Design/   — REQ, decisions, architecture (areas/{{AREA_NAME}}/)
02_Code/     — Modules ({{AREA_NAME}}/{{MODULE_NAME}}/)
03_Test/     — TC, bugs, reports, traceability
```

## Mandatory lifecycle

1. Understand the request
2. Identify impacted files
3. Create or update structured requirements in `Design/`
4. Produce task plan (`TASKS.md` or `PLAN.md`)
5. Implement incrementally in `02_Code/`
6. Add or update tests in `02_Code/.../test/` and `03_Test/`
7. Run available checks
8. Produce validation report when applicable
9. Fix issues if validation gate enabled and score below threshold
10. Stop only when Definition of Done is satisfied

## Quality gate

Do not mark a task complete unless:

- linked REQ acceptance criteria are satisfied
- REQ has Type, MoSCoW, Priority populated
- required tests pass
- public API documented per `{{DOC_COMMENT_STYLE}}`
- validation score ≥ {{VALIDATION_THRESHOLD}} when `VALIDATION_GATE_ENABLED=true`
- known bugs recorded as BUG-XXXX
- final report explains what changed and why

## Key prompts

| Prompt | Purpose |
|--------|---------|
| `#project-setup` | Initial Design structure |
| `#setup-environment` | Module + IDE adapters |
| `#req-create` | Extract requirements |
| `#review-code` | Structured review |
| `#bug-create` | Bug report |
| `#validation-report` | Quality score |
